%I A318233 #21 Apr 23 2026 03:38:14
%S A318233 1,7,58,545,5570,60438,685980,8065107,97554622,1208020814
%N A318233 Difference between numbers of odd-excedance and even-excedance 123-avoiding derangements of [2n].
%C A318233 From _Gareth McCaughan_, Apr 22 2026: (Start)
%C A318233 The excedance of a permutation p is the number of indices such that p(i) > i.
%C A318233 A permutation is 123-avoiding if there are no three indices i<j<k for which p(i)<p(j)<p(k). (End)
%H A318233 Shishuo Fu, Dazhao Tang, Bin Han, and Jiang Zeng, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.08945">Gamma expansions of q-Narayana polynomials, pattern avoidance and the (-1)-phenomenon</a>, arXiv:1805.08945 [math.CO], 2018. See p. 27.
